    "created_at": "2018-08-14T19:47:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-08-14T19:47:32Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`.query('year != 2010)` is explicit but also duplicative of functionality that already exists. Coding and maintaining that imo is more of a burden than the incremental value it provides, especially since `Series` objects typically are unnamed.\r\n\r\nI am not proposing to drop `query` from DataFrame as it is more useful there were your columns will typically be named. If anything the talk about adding `.query` here to a Series is a red herring as I think the biggest confusion is how to leverage a single level of a MultiIndex in a masking operation. "
  },
